────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
> # Show db init help
> prisma-next db init --help
prisma-next db init → Bootstrap a database to match the current contract and sign it
│
│ --json                Output as JSON
│ -q, --quiet           Quiet mode: errors only
│ -v, --verbose         Verbose output: debug info, timings
│ --trace               Trace output: deep internals, stack traces
│ --color               Force color output
│ --no-color            Disable color output
│ --interactive         Force interactive mode
│ --no-interactive      Disable interactive prompts
│ -y, --yes             Auto-accept prompts
│ --db <url>            Database connection string
│ --config <path>       Path to prisma-next.config.ts
│ --dry-run             Preview planned operations without applying
│                       default: false
│
│ Examples:
│   $ prisma-next db init --db $DATABASE_URL
│   $ prisma-next db init --db $DATABASE_URL --dry-run
│
│ Initializes a database to match your emitted contract using additive-only operations.
│ Creates any missing tables, columns, indexes, and constraints defined in your contract.
│ Leaves existing compatible structures in place, surfaces conflicts when destructive changes
│ would be required, and signs the database to track contract state. Use --dry-run to
│ preview changes without applying.
└
